{{- end}}

## SRV Record Support

{{if (or .Features.DB .Features.Cache)}}This application supports DNS SRV record discovery for service location. When connecting to databases or cache services, you can use either:

### Direct Connection
```
host:port
```
Example: `localhost:5432`, `redis.example.com:6379`

### SRV Discovery
```
_service._proto.hostname
```
Example: `_postgresql._tcp.db.cluster`, `_redis._tcp.cache.cluster`

The application will automatically detect the format:
- If the host starts with `_`, it's treated as an SRV name and resolved via DNS
- Otherwise, it's parsed as a direct `host:port` connection
{{- else}}
SRV record support is available but not currently used (no database or cache configured).
{{- end}}

{{- if .Features.DB}}

### Database Connection

```go
import "{{.ModulePath}}/internal/db"

// Using SRV discovery
db, err := db.Connect(log, "_postgresql._tcp.db.cluster", user, password, dbName)

// Using direct connection
db, err := db.Connect(log, "localhost:5432", user, password, dbName)
```
{{- end}}

{{- if and .Features.Cache (eq (toString .CacheType) "redis")}}

### Redis Connection

```go
import "{{.ModulePath}}/internal/redis"

// Using SRV discovery
client, err := redis.NewClient(log, "_redis._tcp.cache.cluster", password, 0)

// Using direct connection
client, err := redis.NewClient(log, "localhost:6379", password, 0)
```
{{- end}}

{{- if and .Features.Cache (eq (toString .CacheType) "valkey")}}

### Valkey Connection

```go
import "{{.ModulePath}}/internal/valkey"

// Using SRV discovery
client, err := valkey.NewClient(log, "_valkey._tcp.cache.cluster", password)

// Using direct connection
client, err := valkey.NewClient(log, "localhost:6379", password)
```
{{- end}}

